President Barack Obama has proclaimed September 2012 as National Preparedness Month in the United States. This proclamation emphasizes the importance of emergency preparedness in homes, businesses, and communities nationwide. The President encourages individuals to visit websites like www.Ready.gov or www.Listo.gov to learn about the risks facing their communities and take action by building a disaster supply kit and developing an emergency plan with their loved ones. The proclamation also acknowledges the recent severe weather events and calls for unity and resilience in the face of future disasters.